      <div class="faq-item open"><div class="faq-q">How long does the {{ product_model | escape }} screen repair take?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Most repairs are completed in 1–2 working days. If you drop in before 11am and the part is in stock, same-day is often possible. Add the {{ fast_price }} fast-turnaround option if you need a guaranteed 1-day return.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are the screens genuine Apple parts?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Yes. Every display we fit is a genuine pulled OEM panel — sourced from first-party Apple stock and recalibrated in-house against a reference sensor. We do not fit aftermarket panels on this model. True Tone, full brightness, and colour accuracy are preserved.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Will my data be safe during the repair?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Yes. Screen repairs don't touch your drive. We run a GDPR-compliant workshop and sign an NDA on request for corporate clients. We never ask for your passcode unless post-repair testing requires it — and you can be present for that step.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What does the 2-year warranty cover?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Functional defects of the display assembly we fitted, the labour, and any re-work needed during the period. Accidental damage isn't covered, but we'll always quote fairly for re-repairs. Apple's own warranty on out-of-warranty screen repair is 90 days, for comparison.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do I need an appointment, or can I walk in?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Either works. Walk in Mon–Fri 9–6 (Fri until 6pm) at 12 Margaret St, W1W 8JQ — opposite The London Palladium. Starting with the quote CTA above gives us the repair details before you arrive.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What if the issue isn't actually the screen?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">We do a free pre-diagnosis before quoting. If it turns out to be the backlight IC, a logic-board fuse, or T-CON corrosion, we'll fix the actual fault — usually for less than a full screen swap. We won't sell you a screen you don't need.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Can you collect from outside London?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Yes. London-area customers can use our courier service ({{ courier_price }} same/next-day collection). UK-wide, we offer free pre-paid mail-in. International courier coming soon.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Will True Tone still work after the repair?<span class="icon">+</span></div><div class="faq-a">Yes. We use a reference colorimeter to flash the True Tone profile onto every display before fitting. Aftermarket panels can't carry the True Tone calibration — that's why we don't fit them.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

